cs.DB, cs.LG, cs.DS, cs.AI, cs.DC 

This paper focuses on efficient counting and data structures for machine learning datasets, which are common topics in the fields of databases (cs.DB), machine learning (cs.LG), and data structures (cs.DS). The paper also discusses the use of these techniques in Bayes net structure finding algorithms, rule learning algorithms, and feature selection algorithms, which are all subfields of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Finally, the paper compares the ADtree method to alternative representations such as kd-trees, R-trees, and Frequent Sets, which are topics in distributed computing (cs.DC).
